
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Louvre Museum Exhibition Management System

class Museum {
  -name: String
  -locations: List<Location>
}

class Location {
  -name: String
  -area: String
  -exhibitions: List<Exhibition>
}

class Exhibition {
  -title: String
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
  -coordinator: Employee
  -items: List<ExhibitionItem>
}

class Employee {
  -id: Integer
  -name: String
  -role: String
  -coach: Employee
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  -description: String
  -desiredPieces: List<Piece>
  -requestedPieces: List<RequestedPiece>
}

class Piece {
  -id: Integer
  -title: String
  -artist: String
  -collector: Collector
}

class Collector {
  -id: Integer
  -name: String
  -pieces: List<Piece>
}

class RequestedPiece {
  -piece: Piece
  -collector: Collector
  -status: String
}

' Relationships
Museum "1" --> "0..*" Location
Location "1" --> "0..*" Exhibition
Exhibition "1" --> "1" Employee : coordinator
Employee "1" --> "0..1" Employee : coach
Exhibition "1" --> "0..*" ExhibitionItem
ExhibitionItem "1" --> "0..*" Piece : desiredPieces
ExhibitionItem "1" --> "0..*" RequestedPiece
Piece "1" --> "1" Collector
RequestedPiece "1" --> "1" Piece
RequestedPiece "1" --> "1" Collector
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Museum**: Manages multiple **Locations**.
- **Location**: Represents a part of the museum (e.g., a floor or wing) that can host **Exhibitions**.
- **Exhibition**: Has a **Coordinator**, a start/end date, and contains **ExhibitionItems**.
- **Employee**: Has a **Coach** (a senior employee), and may be a **Coordinator**.
- **ExhibitionItem**: Describes what is needed in an exhibition and which **Pieces** are desired or requested from **Collectors**.
- **Piece**: An artwork or item, sourced from a **Collector**.
- **Collector**: Maintains a collection of **Pieces**.
- **RequestedPiece**: Tracks which **Piece** was requested from which **Collector** for an **ExhibitionItem**, along with its status.

---

